  .row
    .col-sm-3#toc
      ul
        li
          a(href="#framework") Framework
          ul
            li
              a(href="#readme") Readme
            li
              a(href="#changelog") Changelog
            li
              a(href="#guide") Guide
            li
              a(href="#examples") Examples
            li
              a(href="#reference") Reference

    .col-sm-9#main

      .row.margin-bottom-small
        .col-lg-6
          +headerSubsection({_name: 'Readme', _icon: 'fa-file-text-o', _path: '/readme'})
          p.
            With the help of this section you can learn some basics for getting started,
            the major features of the framework and how to contribute to it.

        .col-lg-6
          +headerSubsection({_name: 'Changelog', _icon: 'fa-clock-o', _path: '/changelog'})
          p.
            In this section we prepare a detailed log of code changes. Keep an eye
            on this section for new features, improvements and bugfixes. Stay tuned!

      .row.margin-bottom-small
        .col-lg-6
          +headerSubsection({_name: 'Guide', _icon: 'fa-book', _path: '/guide'})
          p.
            The guide will push you to the next level of Greppy knowledge. We cover
            fundamentals, deep sub-routine usage, and an overall view of the framework.

        .col-lg-6
          +headerSubsection({_name: 'Cookbook', _icon: 'fa-magic', _path: '/cookbook'})
          p.
            The cookbook covers solutions for common usecases and problems. You will
            find detailed descriptions how to use the solutions without suffer from headaches.

      .row.margin-bottom-small
        .col-lg-6
          +headerSubsection({_name: 'Reference', _icon: 'fa-code', _path: '/reference'})
          p.
            A complete coding experience is guaranteed with this section. Look up
            detailed class outlines with our API reference.

